## Cheat codes `10110101`:

### Markdown ⬇️

Check out [markdown](https://simplemde.com/markdown-guide) or get super fancy and hack some sweet [mdsvex](https://mdsvex.com/), maybe from an external source (npm, ipfs, arweave -- dealer's choice).

### Fork & Borrow 🍴

Don't start from scratch. Surf the [gallery](/blog) for work that others have built, and build cool stuff on top of what they've already built.

### Save! 💾

Your drafts are auto [saved](https://github.com/gruns/ImmortalDB) to the browser and published to Solana at your discretion! This is the decentralized internet. Places like [Arweave](https://www.arweave.org/), [IPFS](https://ipfs.io/), can be used as links in your blogs!

- IPFS: Free, but kinda temporary, sometimes
- Arweave: less than $0.01; >1000 posts for $1
- Solana: less than $0.01; >1000 posts for $1

### Crypto Twitter, Underground

Try searching someone's (case-sensitive) [Twitter username](https://naming.bonfida.org/#/twitter-registration), and if they've created a blog channel under that Public Key, it'll show up.

### Wallet & Keys

By default the SolBlog uses the ever popular [Phantom](https://phantom.app/) to connect, but you could pass in a keypair if you like.

You can use the Wallet on DevNet, all it does it sign transactions for you.

### AirDrop

If you've selected DevNet, and your SOL balance is low (or zero) an AirDrop button pops up so you can fund your account. Sorry, no air drop on mainnet 😉

